Japanese trading house Sumitomo Corp. said Thursday  its consolidated pre-tax earnings declined 6.5 percent from a year earlier to  42.2 billion yen (410 million dollars) in the year to March.
The nucleus of the Osaka-based Sumitomo group of companies said worldwide  sales slipped 5.7 percent to 17,000 billion yen in the same period, depressed  by lower revenue from all areas except metals. Revenue from domestic trading  as well as imports and exports declined, offset by higher overseas revenue.
For the current year, however, the company forecast improved earnings of  45 billion yen on increasd sales of 17,500 billion yen.
